<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Printf on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/printf/</link><description>Recent content in Printf on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/printf/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash Echo: Invalid Option Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-echo-option-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-echo-option-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-echo-invalid-option-error-fix"&gt;Bash Echo: Invalid Option Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A bash echo error occurs when &lt;code&gt;echo&lt;/code&gt; receives an unrecognized option. The behavior of &lt;code&gt;echo&lt;/code&gt; varies between shells and versions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;echo&lt;/code&gt; in bash interprets some flags (&lt;code&gt;-n&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;-e&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;-E&lt;/code&gt;) but not others. Passing an unknown flag like &lt;code&gt;--help&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;-x&lt;/code&gt; produces an error or is treated as literal text depending on the shell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;--&lt;/code&gt; or unsupported flags with echo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portability issues between bash and other shells&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Misunderstanding echo vs printf behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;-e&lt;/code&gt; in scripts that might run on dash/sh&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-use-printf-for-reliable-output"&gt;1. Use printf for reliable output&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: echo with unsupported option&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo -- &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello World&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# May print &amp;#34;-- Hello World&amp;#34; or error&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use printf&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printf &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;%s\n&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello World&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-use-echo-only-with-supported-flags"&gt;2. Use echo only with supported flags&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Known echo flags&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo -n &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;No newline&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo -e &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Tab\there&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Interpret escapes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo -E &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;No escapes&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Don&amp;#39;t interpret escapes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-use-printf-for-format-control"&gt;3. Use printf for format control&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: printf for precise output&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printf &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Name: %s\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$name&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printf &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Count: %03d\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$count&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printf &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Value: %.2f\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$value&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-avoid-echo-for-complex-strings"&gt;4. Avoid echo for complex strings&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Echo with special characters&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$var&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; with spaces and *&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use quotes and printf&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printf &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;%s\n&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$var&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; with spaces and *&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="bash-syntax-error"&gt;Bash Syntax Error&lt;/a&gt; — general syntax issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="unmatched-quote"&gt;Unmatched Quote&lt;/a&gt; — quoting issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="word-splitting"&gt;Word Splitting&lt;/a&gt; — whitespace handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Format string vulnerability</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/format-string-vulnerability/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/format-string-vulnerability/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="format-string-vulnerability"&gt;Format string vulnerability&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A format string vulnerability occurs when user-controlled input is passed as the format string to &lt;code&gt;printf&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;fprintf&lt;/code&gt;, or similar functions. This can cause crashes, information leaks, or arbitrary code execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: User input as format string
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; buf[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fgets&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(buf), stdin);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(buf); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// VULNERABLE — user controls format
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Wrong format specifier
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;%s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, x); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// undefined behavior
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Missing format string
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;msg &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(msg); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// VULNERABLE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-constant-format-string"&gt;Fix 1: Use constant format string&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; buf[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fgets&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(buf), stdin);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;%s&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, buf); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// safe — format is constant
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-correct-format-specifiers"&gt;Fix 2: Use correct format specifiers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;%d&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, x); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; pi &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;%.2f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, pi); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-compile-with-format-protection"&gt;Fix 3: Compile with format protection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gcc -Wformat-security -Wformat -Werror&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;format-security -o prog prog.c
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; input[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Enter your name: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fgets&lt;/span&gt;(input, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(input), stdin);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// SAFE: format string is constant
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, %s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, input);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// UNSAFE: never do this
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// printf(input);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/uninitialized-variable/"&gt;Uninitialized variable&lt;/a&gt; — undefined behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/segmentation-fault-null/"&gt;Segmentation fault&lt;/a&gt; — crash from bad format.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/stack-overflow-recursive/"&gt;Stack overflow&lt;/a&gt; — stack exhaustion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Format String Vulnerability — Warning Format Not a String Literal Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/format-string/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/format-string/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-format-string-vulnerability--warning-format-not-a-string-literal-fix"&gt;[Solution] C Format String Vulnerability — Warning Format Not a String Literal Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;format string vulnerability&lt;/strong&gt; occurs when user-controlled data is passed as the format argument to &lt;code&gt;printf&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;fprintf&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;sprintf&lt;/code&gt;, or similar functions. The compiler warns with &lt;code&gt;warning: format not a string literal and no format arguments&lt;/code&gt; because the &lt;code&gt;%&lt;/code&gt; characters in the input are interpreted as format specifiers, causing crashes (e.g., &lt;code&gt;Segfault&lt;/code&gt; from &lt;code&gt;%n&lt;/code&gt;) or leaking sensitive memory (e.g., &lt;code&gt;%x&lt;/code&gt; printing stack values).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ fmt - formatting error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/fmt-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/fmt-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="fmt---formatting-error"&gt;fmt - formatting error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The fmt library throws errors when format strings are invalid, arguments don&amp;rsquo;t match placeholders, or types are unsupported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Wrong argument count
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; fmt&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;format(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, {} and {}!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// too few args
